article.headline: Penn State 63, Morehead State 46
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Jamelle Cornley scored a game-high 17 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to help Penn State defeat Morehead State 63-46 Friday night in the season opener for each team. Ben Luber chipped in 12 points for the Nittany Lions (1-0), who were playing without leading returning scorer Geary Claxton, who is out until early December with a broken right hand. Danny Morrissey, playing his first game in more than a year after recovering from a knee injury, started in Claxton's place and finished with nine points. The Lions extended a 13-point halftime lead after Cornley made three of his first four shots in the second half to spur the Lions to an 8-2 run. Shaun Williams led Morehead State (0-1) with 18 points. Eagles first-year head coach Donnie Tyndall lost his first game coaching his alma mater. Penn State rebounded from a disappointing loss Monday at home to Division-II Shippensburg in its exhibition season finale.
